wiki.summary: "Centuries" (stylized as "Cen†uries") is a song by American rock band Fall Out Boy, released September 9, 2014 as the lead single from their sixth studio album, American Beauty/American Psycho (2015). It was co-written by Fall Out Boy, with two producers. A Gladiator-themed music video was created. The single reached No. 10 on the US Billboard Hot 100 and was certified 2x Platinum by the RIAA. It reached first position on the UK Rock and Metal Chart. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Centuries" (stylized as "Cen†uries") is a song by American rock band Fall Out Boy, released September 9, 2014 as the lead single from their sixth studio album, American Beauty/American Psycho (2015). It was co-written by Fall Out Boy, with two producers. A Gladiator-themed music video was created. The single reached No. 10 on the US Billboard Hot 100 and was certified 2x Platinum by the RIAA. It reached first position on the UK Rock and Metal Chart. This is also the band's fourth top ten hit and first in eight years since "This Ain't a Scene, It's an Arms Race" in 2007. Fall Out Boy has played the song numerous times on televised performances. The song features samples of Tom's Diner. Read more on Last.fm.
